      "writtenOn": "2020-09-28T13:12:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not sure I like using https://github.com/google/skia-buildbot/blob/0d5a5b4b2895b0aa3fe85fd492fde586da71c6c1/go/git/util.go#L46 here. The Executable call seems a lot more opaque than just me specifying the absolute path to the git executable we want to use. I would argue that we want our task_drivers to be as simple as possible and this line of code leaves fewer surprises than git.Clone would. (additionally, I can\u0027t specify options like --depth 1",
      "parentUuid": "6b234ef6_de7e1f86",
