    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e819948e_3bbc8646",
        "filename": "infra/bots/task_drivers/cifuzz/cifuzz.go",
        "patchSetId": 26
      },
      "lineNbr": 172,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-09-25T19:52:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Docker package requires volume mounts instead of --mount and doesn\u0027t allow me to have the --name or --rm flag.",
      "parentUuid": "e348df29_51342432",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 172,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 172,
        "endChar": 57
      },
      "revId": "130c08cfc92111507d53b54c4e45de00a6d9a66b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "801ff713_b13a087f",
        "filename": "infra/bots/task_drivers/cifuzz/cifuzz.go",
        "patchSetId": 26
      },
      "lineNbr": 172,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-09-28T11:19:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Looking at the current usage of docker.Run, I think we could add --rm by default and change --volume to --mount.  I don\u0027t know the utility of --name when running on CI, but I\u0027m not opposed to adding it, either explicitly or by adding a variadic parameter for any extra flags.",
      "parentUuid": "e819948e_3bbc8646",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 172,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 172,
        "endChar": 57
      },
